identified-content.person: FRANDINA, DR. RACHAEL LYNN (DR. RACHAEL LYNN CAIATI)

block.p: Dr. Rachael Lynn Frandina and Dr. Joseph Michael Caiati Jr., physicians in New York, were married yesterday at St. Louis Roman Catholic Church in Buffalo. The Rev. Mark A. Connolly performed the ceremony.
The bride, who graduated from Macalester College in St. Paul, and the bridegroom, a graduate of Colgate University, received medical degrees from Columbia.

Dr. Rachael Lynn Frandina and Dr. Joseph Michael Caiati Jr., physicians in New York, were married yesterday at St. Louis Roman Catholic Church in Buffalo. The Rev. Mark A. Connolly performed the ceremony.
The bride, who graduated from Macalester College in St. Paul, and the bridegroom, a graduate of Colgate University, received medical degrees from Columbia.

The bride, 29, is an intern in internal medicine at Beth Israel Medical Center. Her father, Anthony F. Frandina of Derby, N.Y., is a vice president and a director of Trubee, Collins & Company, an investment concern in Buffalo. Her mother, Mary Moran Semler of Clarence, N.Y., is the associate director of the Anderson Gallery in Buffalo.

The bridegroom, 32, is a chief resident in surgery at the Columbia-Presbyterian Center of New York Presbyterian Hospital. His father retired as the president of Caiati Home Furnishings, which was a retail chain in Connecticut and New York.
